# netlog replay fixture (issue #160 Phase 2). Each line is a synthetic captured
# egress record ({ts,caller,op,host,port,ok}) in the same shape netlog writes to
# $CRABCC_HOME/netlog.jsonl; `ok` is the EXPECTED allowlist verdict. Allowed =
# real crabcc infra; denied = hosts that must never pass — including
# 169.254.169.254 (the cloud-metadata IP, a classic SSRF/exfil target) and a
# suffix-boundary spoof (github.com.evil.com must NOT match github.com).
#
# Replayed by `task netlog-replay` (and the workspace test run) through the
# enforcer in deny mode against the seeded allowlist. Keep in sync with
# netlog_allowlist.txt: a new allowlist entry that a real caller needs should
# gain an `ok:true` line here; nothing should be added `ok:true` without a
# matching allowlist entry.
